summary: So I watched Marvel with my Dad last night.
body:
So I watched Marvel with my Dad last night.

The only back seats we could get was at the 10:35 showing so we stayed up for a while. We watched the movie and post credit scenes pop up. This is the conversation that followed:


My Dad: Oh. They got dustified?

Me:…Dustified?

My Dad: Yeah, they got dustified?

Me: Alrighty. It’s no longer called the Snap. It’s dustified. They got dustified.

title: Welcome Home
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2OmZx8G

by denyingmyself

Thor laughed bitterly. “We won the war, I suppose. But I lost everything.”

“Your people?”

“And my family. My…” Thor clenched his jaw, “brother.”

Thor could practically hear the question before Peter had even asked it. “Wasn’t he evil?”

He sighed. “Loki… was complicated. He had evil intentions at first, but they were motivated by a broken childhood and an infinity stone’s influence. That and Thanos tortured him. What he did… was not okay, but in the end… he was a hero.”

or: Thor is coping with Loki’s death not the greatest until someone shows up to help
